2004-10-13  Vitaly V. Bursov  <vitalyvb@users.sourceforge.net>
	* configure.ac, drivers/Makefile.am, drivers/null/*:
	Added a null plugin. Note that it generates resize and
	quit events. Check the source.
	* example/main.c: added #if NULL_PLUG, added
	visual_bin_sync() to resize event handler.
	* lvdisplay/lvdisplay.c: poll events in
	lvdisplay_poll_event() not in lvdisplay_run().
	* example/main.c: do not use null plugin by default.
	* drivers/glx/glx_new.c lvdisplay/lv_display.c drivers/glx/glx.c:
	draw framebuffer not upside down, support paletted 8bit mode via
	Libvisual's converter 8bit to 24bits, video buffer pitch fix.
	* lvdisplay/lv_display.c: pass events to backend.
	* drivers/null/null.c drivers/glx/glx.c:
	added event handlers functions and resize event handler
	for non-gl plugins.
	* lvdisplay/lv_display.c: free previous context if
	there's one in lvdisplay_realize().
	* example/main.c: added ability to switch plugins on the fly.

